Inference - The scatter plot shows the relationship between the total number of car crashes and insurance premiums. From the plot, we can observe that there is no clear linear relationship between the two variables. However, we can see that some states with a higher number of accidents tend to have higher insurance premiums, while others have lower premiums despite having a similar number of accidents.
